Who is looking for credit matching my desired risk profile? Who owns land in my VR district and how much did they pay? Today, getting data like this requires you to write your own indexing server that you have to run and operate on centralized DISTRIBUTED QUERY PROCESSING On The Graph, queries are processed on a decentralized network that ensures that data remains open and that dApps continue to run no matter Users don’t have to trust teams to operate servers and developers can deploy to trustworthy public infrastructure they don’t have to GATEWAY NODE QUERY NODES THE FLEXIBILITY OF GRAPHQL The Graph uses GraphQL, a query language developed and by It provides a powerful API to get exactly the data you need in a single request, seamlessly traversing and combining data FAST Build dApps that load lightning Your users will appreciate not having to look at BROAD SUPPORT Popular with web and mobile developers with existing libraries for React, React Native, and COMPOSABLE Create shareable and composable UI components that load data automatically inside any FEATURES FILTERS With boolean expressions PAGINATION First, last, and skip SORTING Asc or desc SUBSCRIPTIONS Websockets BLOCK REORGS Transparently READ MORE AT THE TEAM YANIV Project Lead Twitter Linkedin JANNIS Tech Lead Twitter Linkedin BRANDON Research Lead Twitter Linkedin CARL Design Lead Twitter Linkedin RODRIGO Community Lead Twitter Linkedin NENA Software Engineer Twitter Linkedin FORD Software Engineer Twitter Linkedin LEO Software Engineer Linkedin ADVISORS ESTEBAN ORDANO CTO at Decentraland RICHARD BURTON CEO at Balance ZAKI MANIAN Head of Tendermint Labs JEHAN TREMBACK CEO at Althea A FUTURE FREE FROM DATA SILOS We re building The Graph because we ve seen the challenges in getting data off We envision The Graph as a truly decentralized ecosystem where the community can collaborate on curating quality data sources available to Together we can build a new generation of the web free from data silos and Available soon GET UPDATES Subscribe Thank you for subscribing Error San Francisco, CA   The Graph - We accommodate all experience levels, beginners to Our teaching philosophy is that fieldwork is the best teaching Therefore field trips are the cornerstone of all our This allows for lots of one on one We approach and work with each student at whatever their skill Throughout the workshop and balanced with the field trips are individual reviews and critiques, this allows us to evaluate everyone’s work at whatever their level, and help identify strengths and weaknesses in their technique and visualization If you are an absolute beginner, we suggest you read your cameral manual and try to understand as much about the workings of your camera as you can before you show up for a Practice taking pictures using your This is probably the biggest area that we see students struggling This is especially important for Winter Workshops, where the last thing you want to be doing is struggling with a tripod outside in the Back to top What kind of equipment do I need? All you need is a camera with manual controls for the focus, and exposure settings (or auto with manual overrides) tripod, and cable These are the basics, remember great camera systems don’t make great photographs, great photographers If you are thinking about buying or adding to your existing system, contact us and talk with us about your equipment needs before you purchase, we may be able to save you money and Back to top Do I need special camera equipment? No, and yes and Great flower photographs can be made with a minimum of equipment, it is one of the things that makes wildflower photography so much You can spend a lot of money on macro lenses and other gadgets for photography, you can also enjoy macro photography without spending an arm and a leg on We will demonstrate techniques that do not require expensive equipment yet allow you to explore the exciting world of Back to top Besides camera equipment what other gear will I need? It depends upon the workshop location, and We will send you a confirmation letter with detailed information about equipment and workshop Back to top What if I want to shoot B&W film? Great! We have extensive B&W I photographed for over years in B&W before I made a serious color We have complete B&W enlarging capabilities (up to ×24 inches) in our I have worked as a commercial and fine art B&W However, some workshops may not allow for the processing of B&W film during the Back to top Are these workshops geared towards film or digital shooters? Currently most of our participants are shooting If you are film shooter contact us to determine the facilities available for processing your Because we spend a lot of individual time with the student, we are able to address technical issues for both mediums on an individual need to know basis in all of our workshops . We have a laptop for downloading and viewing images from field Digital shooters should remember to bring all software, drivers, cords, and camera manuals when attending any Back to top Do you supply transportation? For most workshops we do not supply transportation, unless specifically If transportation is an issue, contact us and we may be able to help you arrange carpooling with another We are generally not available ourselves, as we arrive a day or two early to most workshop Back to top What is a typical itinerary for a workshop? What’s a Good Breeder? | Learn About Our Standards | Good Dog Learning Center Breed Explorer Our Standards Contact a Specialist What s a Good Breeder? What s a Good Breeder? One of the most important choices you’ll face when becoming a dog owner is where to get your new Working with a responsible breeder can lead to a lifetime of happiness with your dog, while cutting corners or getting tricked by unethical sources may result in years of complications, like serious behavioral issues or or health problems and medical A responsible breeder gives you the best chance for adding a happy, healthy member to your family because they, too, care for their dogs like Their goal is to bring healthy, dogs into the world and to make sure they go to warm and caring It starts even before the actual breeding, when breeders make sure that the parent dogs are strong, healthy, and have characteristics that should be passed along to the next generation of There isn t a singular blueprint to determine a Good Ethical and unethical programs come in all kinds of sizes and The only marker of a reputable breeder is quality of Each family may prioritize different things and have different aspects of a breeder they care most It’s our hope that Good Dog s full and transparent presentation of each breeder and their practices will allow you to understand the big picture and choose a breeder that is right for Unfortunately, spotting a responsible breeder can be difficult without the right knowledge and That’s why we’ve worked with leading veterinary, academic and breeding experts to create a set of standards that we use to evaluate all breeders before recognizing them as a Good Breeder and listing them on Good We’ve outlined below what it means to be a Good Breeder, but we also want to encourage everyone looking for a dog to feel comfortable asking breeders questions directly as The process of finding the right dog and breeder can be a long and arduous You should feel empowered to ask all kinds of questions to every breeder you speak Most reputable breeders will be thrilled to talk at length and answer any kinds of questions you have about their program or their Inquire about specific health issues and testing for the breed you’re looking into getting, temperament, training, socialization, and Each person will have different needs and prioritize different attributes of a breeder so it’s key to ask questions to determine if you’re working with a breeder that is the right fit for you and your We’ll also be here every step of the way to help you know what questions to ask, understand the answers, and make the best decision for Good Breeders Careful screening based on science Every breeder on Good Dog is individually screened and recognized for responsible breeding Before being approved to join Good Dog, we speak with every breeder personally and carefully review their knowledge, practices, and Good intentions and education We make sure that breeders don t just have their hearts in the right place but are also in the right practices around vet care and Good Breeders are committed to learning and improving so they constantly educate themselves on new and better practices when it comes to health They prioritize their dogs above all A lifelong commitment The breeders on Good Dog are committed to keeping their dogs out of the shelter For this reason, breeders spend a great deal of time making sure each dog is a good fit for their new Should anything come up, Good Dog requires that breeders take back their dogs and rehome them if Responsible breeders thoroughly vet the homes their dogs will be going to and they’ll always take one of their dogs back if an issue or an emergency Prioritizes the of their dogs The goal of every reputable breeding program is to put the emotional and physical health of their dogs above all The adult dogs and puppies in each program receive the very best From 3 weeks to weeks, puppies go through a crucial socialization During the early portion of this period, breeders gently expose their puppies to all kinds of people, animals, noises, and environments to make sure they re behaviorally and emotionally healthy when they head to their new Then breeder guide their owners to complete their pup’s development through Our standards are just the beginning The breeders on Good Dog treat their dogs like family and take pride in giving them the very best Their programs are designed to nurture their puppies in every way — this includes socialization and enrichment that begins at a very young age so they re fully prepared to enter their new Each breeder takes the extra step to match their puppy with a family who will be a good This ensures that the puppy and their new owners will be able to get along in both lifestyle and temperament and sets them up for success from the Read more about our community standards and screening Read our full Good Breeder Code of Ethics Vaccine Program: ​ Hemagglutinin (HA) is the primary protein on the surface of the Influenza virus that the immune system mounts antibodies The “head” domain of HA is highly variable: it mutates and changes each season, and as a result, current Influenza vaccines are , meaning that they each only protect against one prevalent, seasonal For this reason new vaccine cocktails must be designed and manufactured before each winter In contrast, the “stalk” domain of HA is highly conserved across Influenza strains and antibodies generated against the stalk of HA therefore protect against many However, the head domain acts as a decoy and distracts the immune system from reacting to the stalk and as a result very few stalk antibodies are elicited in infected For this reason, there has been a concerted effort in the Influenza vaccine field to design a “Headless-HA” vaccine consisting of only the conserved stalk domain, with the head domain Headless HA would focus immune responses on only the highly conserved stalk domain and thus elicit broad protection not just against multiple strains of seasonal influenza, but also against the risk of future pandemic influenza To date, it has otherwise not been technically feasible in the field to design a Headless HA molecule comprising the HA stalk trimer, that is correctly folded in its native prefusion Calder has used DT conformational locking to render this ​ By introducing DT crosslinks into the stalk of HA, Calder first locks the stalk of HA in its native, trimeric, prefusion Then, once the stalk is locked, we remove the head domain with a protease, using targeted engineered cleavage The resulting molecule, ‘DT-Headless HA’ can be produced at high yields, and shows intact stalk antigenicity: it binds to a panel of key stalk antibodies but does not bind to HA is now being manufactured in our lab so it can be tested in mouse immunogenicity We aim to demonstrate that HA elicits broad protection against multiple influenza We are currently exploring further funding for preclinical and clinical We estimate a $2B+ billion market opportunity between seasonal and pandemic Calder is collaborating with James Crowe, , Director, Vanderbilt Vaccine Center and with Indresh Srivastava, , Vice President, Product Realization, Protein Sciences , now Sanofi This work is funded by SBIR grant who we are TECHNOLOGIES Oct , Press Release | Quanta Therapeutics Press Release Quanta Therapeutics Announces Oversubscribed $60 Million Series C Financing to Advance Novel Programs Series C Financing Led by Surveyor Capital (a Citadel company) and Vida Ventures Differentiated mechanisms target RAS active conformation across all mutant forms, with potential to circumvent resistance mechanisms experienced with first generation KRAS inhibitors October , San Francisco, California, October , — Quanta Therapeutics, , a biopharmaceutical company pioneering therapies to treat cancer types, today announced that it has successfully closed a $60 Million Series C financing round led by Surveyor Capital (a Citadel company) and Vida New investors Longitude Capital and BVF Partners joined existing investors Sofinnova Investments, Logos Capital, AbbVie Ventures, and Vida Ventures (who also led Quanta’s Series B financing round). “We are thrilled to have this unique opportunity to partner with a investor base as we merge novel protein structural insights, leading technology in detection of conformational drug activity, and sophisticated medicinal chemistry expertise to develop differentiated therapeutics for the benefit of patients suffering from cancers,” said Perry Nisen, MD, PhD, Quanta Chief Executive “This influx of capital will allow us to continue advancing rational strategies to expand the breadth and duration of benefit for patients with poor existing options and we look forward to the next chapter of growth for ” The company was founded in by Sofinnova Investments, alongside and scientific luminary Frank McCormick, PhD, FRS, with the goal to build a platform that allosterically targets previously undruggable driver oncoprotein signaling Quanta had previously raised $32 Million while in stealth since its inception in “As all oncogenic forms of RAS undergo conformational change to drive functional effector interactions, there was a clear Achilles’ heel in targeting these shared interactions in the active conformation with our platform”, said Cameron Pitt, PhD, Quanta Chief Business Officer & “Founded on compelling science, Quanta’s novel approach has the potential to transform the treatment paradigm for patients with RAS mutations, activated in nearly a third of all human cancers,” said Arjun Goyal, MD, and Managing Director, Vida “We are proud to support this experienced and accomplished team of scientists and biotech executives as they advance their bold vision to address this important unmet need for patients ” The Company will use proceeds from this financing round to advance programs targeting RAF1 and KRAS through clinical candidate selection, and IND filing, to reach initial Leveraging a differentiated mechanism targeting the active conformation of RAS, the Quanta team believes their unique approach, with applicability across mutant RAS forms, will circumvent resistance mechanisms experienced with first generation inhibitors of KRAS About Quanta Quanta Therapeutics, is a biopharmaceutical company focused on direct approaches targeting the protein interactions key to oncogenic RAS RAS is the most prevalent and elusive target in Quanta’s success thus far has driven by their uniquely developed platform, applying Second Harmonic Generation (SHG) optical technology to identify modulators of conformation in drug screening and yielding unparalleled sensitivity to detect change in functional The Quanta team has extensive drug development expertise and substantial research experience in the RAS Application of unique protein conformation detection technology and medicinal chemistry expertise is anticipated to yield novel small molecules as precision medicines designed to address the resistance paradigms of targeted therapy in Learn more at https: www.quantatx.com . IOTA announces software upgrade to silence decentralization critics - Decrypt Menu News Learn Startup Profiles Emails Reading Search About IOTA announces software upgrade to silence decentralization critics cryptocurrency IOTA claims to have a solution to its “coordinator problem,”which has seen critics accuse it of being centralized and not censorship By Adriana Hamacher Cryptocurrencies 2 min read May , May , IOTA, the cryptocurrency, has finally confirmed that it has a solution to its “coordinator ” Until now, IOTA, which is worth over $1 billion, according to CoinMarketCap , and is backed by German engineering giant Bosch , has needed a coordinator—a security mechanism that ensures transaction finality and prevents —to protect the network against This has opened it up to criticism for its lack of censorship Today, IOTA confirmed that it has a solution and will soon implement a protocol upgrade: “Coordicide,” a new, decentralized mechanism for securing the “We have been working towards the removal of the Coordinator since IOTA’s inception,” said David Sønstebø, of IOTA “Now, we are bringing that promise to With this major milestone, we are poised to accelerate into our next phase of growth and enterprise adoption in the real ” IOTA believes that the upgrade will propel it into a new dimension and enable it to become the first technology to solve the holy trinity of fundamental problems that blockchain currently faces: high fees, scaling and IOTA didn’t reveal too many details with respect to how the technology will The company did say, however, that the upgrade will introduce a “modular system that adds flexibility across all aspects of the IOTA ” A white paper is to be released, with more details of how the new protocol will IOTA promises that the new upgrade will provide “increased scalability, faster transaction finality and easier node maintenance,” as well as a variety of novel use These are likely to include services and other IOTA maintains that such uses are currently not feasible in other systems featuring DLT . IOTA, headquartered in Germany, believes its advantage lies in using a drastically different model from a “traditional” Instead of organizing transactions in blocks, IOTA uses something called a “Tangle” to organize devices into nodes, connected via overlapping Its developers claim that this approach enables the possibility of 1,000 transactions per second without any fees The network, which is governed by the IOTA Foundation, also announced that it has recently expanded its research team and founded the IOTA Research Council .
